2016年10月24日，三名全副武装的恐怖分子[[恐怖袭击|袭击]]巴基斯坦[[奎達|奎達]]的俾路支省警察培训学院。造成62名学员死亡、超过165人受伤<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1291999/60-killed-in-twin-suicide-attacks-as-terrorists-storm-police-training-college-in-quetta|title=60 killed in twin suicide attacks as terrorists storm police training college in Quetta|first1=Syed Ali|last1=Shah|first2=Hafeezullah|last2=Sherani|date=2016-10-24|publisher=Dawn|language=en|accessdate=2016-10-25|archive-date=2016-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025174458/http://www.dawn.com/news/1291999/60-killed-in-twin-suicide-attacks-as-terrorists-storm-police-training-college-in-quetta|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="auto1">{{cite web|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1208735/militants-attack-police-training-centre-quetta/|title=61 killed, at least 165 injured as militants storm police training centre in Quetta|date=2016-10-24|publisher=The Express Tribune|accessdate=2016-10-25|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026165023/http://tribune.com.pk/story/1208735/militants-attack-police-training-centre-quetta/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=At Least 61 Die as Militants Storm Police College Near Quetta, Pakistan|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/25/world/asia/quetta-police-militants-attack.html|publisher=The New York Times|date=2016-10-24|accessdate=2016-10-25|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025013556/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/25/world/asia/quetta-police-militants-attack.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[伊斯兰国呼罗珊省|伊斯兰国呼罗珊省]]声称对这起恐怖袭击负责，巴基斯坦的逊尼派穆斯林激进组织[[羌城軍|羌城軍]]声称是跟前者合作<ref name="auto">{{cite web|title=Quetta attack survivor: 'We were sleeping when terrorists attacked'|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/10/24/world/pakistan-police-academy-attack/index.html|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2016-10-25|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025235521/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/10/24/world/pakistan-police-academy-attack/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="collaborated">[http://nation.com.pk/national/26-Oct-2016/lej-collaborated-with-isis-for-quetta-attack LeJ 'collaborated with ISIS' for Quetta attack] {{Wayback|url=http://nation.com.pk/national/26-Oct-2016/lej-collaborated-with-isis-for-quetta-attack |date=20161028112405 }}, The Nation, 26 October 2016.</ref>。巴基斯坦当局称，袭击者来自[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]并在接头人的指引下发起袭击<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1292349/assailants-came-from-afghanistan-pm-told|title=Assailants came from Afghanistan, PM told|work=Dawn|date=26 October 2016|accessdate=2016-10-26|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026232003/http://www.dawn.com/news/1292349/assailants-came-from-afghanistan-pm-told|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 袭击 ==
三名武装分子在周二10月24日晚上11:10闯入培训中心。由于事发时间为晚上，学员们都在睡觉。武装份子趁机挟持数百名学员作为人质与安全部队对峙<ref name="auto1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/At-least-60-killed-over-100-injured-in-Pak-police-academy-attack/articleshow/55042406.cms|title=At least 60 killed, over 100 injured in Pak police academy attack|date=2016-10-25|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=2016-10-25|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025041454/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/At-least-60-killed-over-100-injured-in-Pak-police-academy-attack/articleshow/55042406.cms|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这起恐怖袭击至少造成61人死亡，超过165人受伤<ref name="auto"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Quetta attack death toll rises to 61, over 165 injured|url=http://www.samaa.tv/pakistan/2016/10/quetta-attack-death-toll-rises-to-61-over-160-injured/|website=samaa.tv|publisher=Samaa Web Desk|accessdate=2016-10-25|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025235943/http://www.samaa.tv/pakistan/2016/10/quetta-attack-death-toll-rises-to-61-over-160-injured/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="rt">{{cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/news/363951-pakistan-cadets-hostage-militants/|title=50 killed, dozens injured in attack on Pakistani police training center – reports|publisher=Russia Today|accessdate=2016-10-24|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024235001/https://www.rt.com/news/363951-pakistan-cadets-hostage-militants/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="bbc">{{cite web|title=Quetta police college attack leaves dozens dead|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-37757914|website=bbc.com|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2016-10-24|language=en|archive-date=2016-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025033928/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-37757914|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

三名武装分子均在袭击中丧生。其中两名引爆{{tsl|en|Explosive belt|炸药腰带|自杀腰带}}自杀，另一个由警方射杀。之所以会出现那么多受害者正是因为被犯人的自杀腰带爆炸所波及到的。<ref name="bbc"/>

== 犯人 ==
奎达{{tsl|en|Frontier Corps|邊境兵團}}的兵團長謝爾·阿富罕少將（{{lang|ur|شیر افگن}}；{{lang|en|Sher Afgan}}）声称，实施这起袭击的主谋是巴基斯坦的逊尼派穆斯林激进组织[[羌城軍|羌城軍]]。不久之后，[[伊斯兰国呼罗珊省|伊斯兰国呼罗珊省]]通过[[阿马克新闻社|阿马克新闻社]]宣称对这起袭击负责，并且公布了攻击者的照片。<ref name=CNN>[http://edition.cnn.com/2016/10/24/world/pakistan-police-academy-attack/?sr=google_news Quetta attack survivor: 'We were sleeping when terrorists attacked'] {{Wayback|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/10/24/world/pakistan-police-academy-attack/?sr=google_news |date=20161027061505 }}, CNN, 25 October 2016.</ref><ref name=NYT>{{cite news |author=Salman Masood |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/26/world/asia/quetta-attack-isis-pakistan.html?_r=0 |title=Pakistan Reels After Attack on Police Training College Leaves 61 Dead |publisher=The New York Times |date=2016-10-25 |accessdate=2016-10-30 |archive-date=2016-10-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030041649/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/26/world/asia/quetta-attack-isis-pakistan.html?_r=0 }}</ref><ref name=Reuters>{{cite web |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-pakistan-attack-idUSKCN12O2M6 |title=Islamic State claims attack on Pakistan police academy, 59 dead |date=2016-10-25 |publisher= |accessdate=2016-10-25 |via=Reuters |language=en |archive-date=2019-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107032216/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-pakistan-attack-idUSKCN12O2M6 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Diplomat">Kunwar Khuldune Shahid, [http://thediplomat.com/2016/10/quetta-police-college-attack-pakistan-is-increasingly-vulnerable-to-terrorism/ Quetta Police College Attack: Pakistan Is Increasingly Vulnerable to Terrorism] {{Wayback|url=http://thediplomat.com/2016/10/quetta-police-college-attack-pakistan-is-increasingly-vulnerable-to-terrorism/ |date=20161027121027 }}, The Diplomat, 25 October 2016.</ref>

高级安全官员声称ISIL把这次袭击任务[[外判|外包]]给[[羌城軍|羌城軍]]<ref name="NYT"/>。羌城軍下屬派系阿拉米发言人告诉[[路透社|路透社]]：該組織和伊斯蘭國一起完成了这次袭击<ref name="collaborated"/>分析人士表示，ISIL显然已经在巴基斯坦与当地团体一起合作。<ref name="Reuters"/>。

== 后续 ==
巴基斯坦总理[[納瓦茲·謝里夫|納瓦茲·謝里夫]]取消他所有的活动并会见奎达军队官员<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dunyanews.tv/en/Pakistan/358213-PM-postpones-all-engagements-after-Quetta-police-a |title="PM postpones all engagements after Quetta police academy attack" |access-date=2016-10-30 |archive-date=2016-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027093617/http://dunyanews.tv/en/Pakistan/358213-PM-postpones-all-engagements-after-Quetta-police-a }}.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/159798-PM-Nawaz-to-chair-security-meeting-in-Quetta |title="PPM Nawaz to chair security meeting in Quetta" |access-date=2016-10-30 |archive-date=2016-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027130415/https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/159798-PM-Nawaz-to-chair-security-meeting-in-Quetta }}.</ref>。巴基斯坦国家安全顾问{{tsl|en|Naseer Khan Janjua|江諸華}}通知美国駐巴大使{{Link-en|大衛·黑爾 (美國外交官)|David Hale (diplomat)|大衛·黑爾}}：[[印度研究分析室|印度研究分析室]]和阿富汗[[國家安全局_(阿富汗)|國家安全局]]均有“贊助”巴基斯坦恐怖组织攻擊软目标，并强调对激进份子采取有效行动的必要性<ref><cite class="citation news">[http://nation.com.pk/national/26-Oct-2016/raw-nds-patronising-terror-groups-in-afghanistan "'RAW, NDS patronising terror groups in Afghanistan'"] {{Wayback|url=http://nation.com.pk/national/26-Oct-2016/raw-nds-patronising-terror-groups-in-afghanistan |date=20161030052030 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news">[http://www.dawn.com/news/1292399/ "RAW, NDS patronising terror groups in Afghanistan, national security adviser tells US envoy"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1292399/ |date=20161029141613 }}. </cite></ref>。

